1.title: The Country Bears

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

1.plot: Tackles the very first theatrical movie ever based on a park attraction, 2002's fascinatingly terrible "The Country Bears."

2.title: Ten Years of Disney's California Adventure

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

2.plot: Ten years after Disneyland paved a parking lot and put up Paradise (Pier), Some Jerk With A Camera examines the first decade of the evolution of Disney's California Adventure Park, and why they're doing very little to celebrate their tencennial.

3.title: Star Tours: The Original 1987 Classic

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: What happens when a Jerk, an Idiot and a Spazz team up to review the greatest defunct Tomorrowland thrill ride EVER? No, not that one. No, not that one either. I'm talking about the original STAR TOURS! Join Some Jerk With A Camera, The Wire of The Idiot's Lantern, and SpazzMaster on a thoroughly confounding mystical journey through a galaxy far far away, but somehow right over there somewhere.

6.title: Captain EO Part One

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: At long last, Some Jerk With A Camera tackles the single most bewilderingly inexplicable 3D movie Michael Jackson, George Lucas and Francis Ford Coppola EVER created for the Disney parks! Fasten your non-existent seatbelts, 1980s fans, and get ready for CAPTAIN EO to change the freakin' world!

8.title: Halloween Time at Disneyland

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: Examines Disneyland's annual celebration (or lack thereof) of Halloween, and such seasonal makeovers as Space Mountain Ghost Galaxy and Haunted Mansion Holiday.

9.title: It's a Small World Holiday: Part One

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: They said it couldn't, wouldn't and shouldn't be done, but damned if that's ever stopped Some Jerk With A Camera before. In his season one finale, Jerk finally swallows his pride, casts his doubts into denial, and plunges headfirst into the holiday overlay of "It's A Small World," unquestionably the single most psychotically annoying ride ever devised by man or beast, and lives to tell the tale.

10.title: It's a Small World Holiday: Part Two

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Theme park reviewer Some Jerk With A Camera and theme park ride It's A Small World Holiday continue their fight to the death on each other in part two of what is (with ever-increasing inaccuracy) being called Some Jerk's three-part holiday special!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

11.plot: The conclusion of the epic trilogy of struggle against the force of pure darkness and evil in the universe that is It's a Small World.

3.title: Thirty Years of Epcot Part One: Concept and Opening

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: Some Jerk With A Camera is back once again, with part one of a three-part retrospective on the history of one of the most frustrating experimental prototype communities of tomorrow Disney has ever tried to not really build, EPCOT! In this episode, how the idea came into being, and how death mutated the idea into something completely different.

4.title: Thirty Years of EPCOT Part Two: The 1980s

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

4.plot: A retrospective on the history of Epcot (Center, that is) with a look at the initial public reaction to the park, and how the 1980s tried in vain to enhance it.

5.title: Thirty Years of EPCOT Part Three: The 1990s and 2000s

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

5.plot: Some Jerk With A Camera concludes his three-part retrospective on the first thirty years of EPCOT with a look at the park's replacement attractions of the 1990s and 2000s, and its failed attempts to change its image.

6.title: The Walt Disney Family Museum

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: On April Fool's Day, Some Jerk With A Camera tries to present a thoughtful, in-depth analysis of the Disney family's most elaborate tribute to one of the 20th century's greatest cultural icons, The Walt Disney Family Museum in San Francisco.

7.title: ABC Goes to Disney World!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

7.plot: Jerk delves into the history of Disney's relationship with ABC in this introductory episode of Some Jerk With A Camera's massive retrospective of all the ABC sitcoms that went to Disney World in the mid-'90s.

8.title: Full House Goes to Disney World!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: An ABC retrospective in earnest targeting Full House and its 1993 two-part season six finale, "The House Meets The Mouse," in which the Tanners have a suspiciously eventful Walt Disney World vacation.

9.title: Family Matters Goes to Disney World!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: Some Jerk With A Camera continues his "ABC Goes To Disney World" sitcom episode review series with FAMILY MATTERS and its Urkelicious season six two-parter, "We're Going To Disney World," in which Urkel uses science-magic to turn himself into a real boy! Also, Carl is in it!

10.title: Roseanne Goes to Disney World!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Some Jerk With A Camera continues his "ABC Goes To Disney World" retrospective with a review of the Connor family's trip to Disney World in Roseanne's season eight episode "Disney World War II," along with the three - count 'em, THREE - surrounding episodes that set up or called back to it. It'll be Roseanne-tastic! (LEGAL DISCLAIMER: Review might not actually be Roseanne-tastic)

11.title: Step by Step Goes to Disney World!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

11.plot: Some Jerk With A Camera's review of the "We're Going To Disney World" two-part episode of Step By Step, the occasionally-remembered '90s sitcom starring Bobby from Dallas, Chrissy from Three's Company, and presumably other characters as well.

12.title: Boy Meets World Meets Disney World!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

12.plot: Some Jerk With A Camera continues his ABC/Disney World retrospective with a review of the most beloved, cherished, iconic '90s sitcom to ever be temporarily replaced by Muppets Tonight, Boy Meets World and its Disney World episode "The Happiest Show On Earth!

13.title: Sabrina the Teenage Witch Goes to Disney World!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

13.plot: Some Jerk With A Camera finally reviews the very last '90s ABC sitcom to visit Disney World, Sabrina the Teenage Witch and her season two episode/Animal Kingdom commercial, "Disneyworld!"

14.title: ABC Goes to DisneyLAND!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

14.plot: In this spine-tingling conclusion (at long last) to Some Jerk's seemingly-endless ABC Retrospective, Jerk "returns" to the west coast to review the relatively recent George Lopez and Modern Family Disneyland episodes.

15.title: GOLDMARK AFTER DARK: The Album!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

15.plot: After leaving Disneyland forever, Some Jerk With A Camera returns to his roots as a comedy musician.

16.title: Season Two Outtakes Special Hosted by Kill Bosby!

episode of.title: Some Jerk with a Camera (TV Series 2011– )

16.plot: Dr. Killiam Lucifer Bosby Jr., Ed.D. has returned from regions beyond to deliver unto you foolish mortals all the very best alternate takes, deleted jokes, bloopers and general goofaloofs from the last two years' worth of Some Jerk With A Camera episodes!
